In a normal, low risk pregnancy, use the 4-1-1 rule when deciding when to go to the hospital.

When contractions are coming every 4-5 minutes, lasting 1 min long and have been for 1 hour.

Remember, subsequent labors usually go faster.

When to call the doctor:

- Signs of premature (before 37 weeks) labor

- Leaking or a gush of fluid from the vagina

- When contractions are becoming longer, stronger & closer

- If you have questions or concerns

NEVER feel bad about calling your doctor
